    <h1>Streams</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Abelson &amp; Sussman · 1996 · <a href="https://mitp-content-server.mit.edu/books/content/sectbyfn/books_pres_0/6515/sicp.zip/full-text/book/book-Z-H-24.html#%_sec_3.5">SICP §3.5</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Delayed evaluation lets you work with infinite sequences. Streams are lazy lists: <code>cons-stream</code> delays the cdr. You get the modularity of sequences without the cost of computing everything upfront.</p>
    </div>

